        <h1 style="font-family:Arial; text-align:center; color:#ffffff">Philip K. Dick</h1>
        <h3 style="font-family:Arial; text-align:center; color:#ffffff"><em>"The Most Brilliant Sci-Fi Mind on Any Planet"</em></h3>
      </div>
      <div>
        <center><img src="https://desultoryheroics.files.wordpress.com/2015/08/philip-k-dick1.jpeg"/></center>
        <p style="font-family:Arial; color:#ffffff; text-align:center">Over his prolific career, Philip K. Dick wrote 44 novels and 121 short stories. He died of a stroke at the young age of 53.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="background-color:#bababa; border-radius:10px; margin:50px">
      <h3 style="font-family:Arial; color:#ffffff; text-align:center; padding-top:15px">Notable Works</h3>
      <ul style="margin-left:300px; font-family:Arial">
        <li>"Beyond Lies the Wub", first published short story, published in 1952</li>
        <li>"Solar Lottery", first published novel, published in 1955</li>
        <li>"Man in the High Castle", Hugo award winner, published in 1965</li>
        <li>"Flow My Tears, the Policeman Said", John W. Campbell Award winner in 1974</li>
      </ul>
